<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, BUMPER AND RUNNING BOARDS - MXT - REMOVE AND INSTALL - Headlight, Sealed Beam and
        Turn Signal Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="10">
        <title>Headlight, Sealed Beam and Turn Signal Assembly</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The headlight/turn signals are mounted on the front of the hood on either side of the grille.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight and Sealed Beam - Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to Figure 28 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the headlight wiring harness connector (Item 1) from chassis harness
                    connector (Item 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901328" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901328.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Headlight Connector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT WIRING HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHASSIS WIRING HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 29 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four headlight mounting bolts (Item 3) from underside of hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901329" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901329.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="168px"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Headlight Assembly Mounting Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the remaining headlight assembly follow steps 2-3 above.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to Figure 30 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws (Item 2) from headlight bezel (Item 1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bezel (Item 1).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901330" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901330.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Headlight Bezel Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT BEZEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BEZEL MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 31 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four screws (Item 1) and the bezel plate (Item 2) from around the sealed beam
                    (Item 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901331" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901331.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Bezel Plate Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BEZEL PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SEALED BEAM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 32 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove sealed beam (Item 1) from sealed beam housing (Item 2).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901332" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901332.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Sealed Beam Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SEALED BEAM</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SEALED BEAM HOUSING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 33 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove harness connector (Item 2) from sealed beam (Item 1).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901333" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901333.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Harness Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SEALED BEAM</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <title>Turn Signal Bulb Replacement</title>
            </para>
            <figure id="f0901334" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901334.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Turn Signal Connector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TURN SIGNAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 34 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <para>1.&#9;Remove the turn signal connector (Item 2) from the headlight assembly (Item 1) by twisting it
                counterclockwise and pulling straight out.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0901335" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901335.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Turn Signal Bulb</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TURN SIGNAL BULB</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TURN SIGNAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 35 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <para>2. Remove the bulb (Item 1) from the connector (Item 2).</para>
            <para>3. Install a new bulb (Item 1) into the connector (Item 2)</para>
            <para>Refer to Figure 34 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <para>4. Install the turn signal connector (Item 2) into the headlight assembly (Item 1) and twist it
                clockwise until it locks.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Headlight Bulb Replacement</title>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform this procedure only if vehicle is not equipped with a sealed beam.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to Figure 36 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <para>1.&#9;Remove the harness connector (Item 1), and rubber boot (Item 2) from the headlight assembly
                (Item 3)
            </para>
            <figure id="f0901336" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901336.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 36.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RUBBER BOOT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Refer to Figure 37 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <para>2. Loosen the mounting spring (Item 4) and remove the HB2 bulb assembly (Item 5).</para>
            <figure id="f0901337" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0901337.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 37.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>4. MOUNTING SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEADLIGHT BULB ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>3. Replace the HB2 bulb assembly (Item 5) and secure with the mounting spring (Item 4).</para>
            <para>Refer to Figure 36 for items in parentheses.</para>
            <para>4. Install the rubber boot (Item 2) and harness connector (Item 1) to the headlight assembly (Item
                3).
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Headlight and Sealed Beam - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect harness connector (Item 2, Figure 33) to sealed beam (Item 1, Figure 33).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install sealed beam (Item 1, Figure 32) into sealed beam housing (Item 2, Figure 32).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the sealed beam (Item 3, Figure 31) to the bezel plate (Item 2, Figure 31) with
                    four screws (Item 1, Figure 31).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install headlight bezel (Item 1, Figure 30) with four screws (Item 2, Figure 30).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure headlight assembly from the back with four headlight mounting bolts (Item 3,
                    Figure 29).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the headlight wiring harness (Item 2, Figure 28) to the connector (Item 1,
                    Figure 28).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood back and secure with the hood latches.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
